# Prism Catalyst – Project Conventions

## What This Is
Real-time financial analytics and trading dashboard: Node/Express + Python ML services, React frontend, PostgreSQL/MongoDB/Redis. See [README.md](README.md) for full scope.

## Directory Layout
- **backend/api-service** – Express.js REST API (TypeScript)
- **backend/websocket-service** – Real-time streaming
- **backend/data-pipeline** – Python ETL / ingestion
- **frontend/src** – React app (components, pages, hooks, services, utils)
- **ml-models/** – Sentiment, prediction, optimization (Python)
- **infrastructure/** – Terraform, Docker, optional Kubernetes
- **tests/** – unit, integration, e2e

## Tech Choices
- Backend API: Node 18+, TypeScript, Express. Auth: JWT, OAuth 2.0.
- Frontend: React 18+, TypeScript, Redux Toolkit or Zustand, D3/Recharts/Plotly, Material-UI or Tailwind.
- Python: 3.10+, FastAPI for services, Pandas/NumPy/scikit-learn/PyTorch for ML.
- **PostgreSQL**: Supabase (use Supabase connection string or pooler; schema in docs/architecture/database-schemas.md).
- Use parameterized queries only; no raw string interpolation in SQL. No secrets in repo; use env or a secrets manager.

## Performance Targets (from README)
- API p95 &lt; 100ms; WebSocket &lt; 50ms; chart render &lt; 500ms for 1k+ points; ML inference &lt; 200ms.

## Workflow
- Proceed one deliverable at a time; agent states when to commit before moving on.
- Prefer minimal comments; add comments only for non-obvious logic, security-sensitive code, or critical business rules.
